    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hey, I ran into this after upgrading to 0.12.1 — `timer_start()` callbacks seem to never fire when nvim runs as a child process inside a PTY job. The child just hangs forever.\n\nI noticed it because `vim-startuptime` stopped working (stuck at 0%), but the issue is in nvim itself.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\nIn any nvim instance, run:\n\n```vim\n:call jobstart([v:progpath, '-u', 'NONE', '-c',\n  \\ 'call timer_start(0, {-> execute(\"qall!\")})'], {'pty': v:true})\n```\n\nThe child nvim should quit right away, but it hangs instead. Swapping in a direct `-c 'qall!'` works fine — so the child does start, it's just that the timer never fires.\n\n`vim.defer_fn()` is affected too (makes sense since it uses `timer_start` internally).\n\n## Tested this pretty thoroughly\n\nAll with `-u NONE`, no plugins, no user config.\n\n### 0.12.1 as child — timers broken in PTY\n\n| Quit method | PTY | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| `timer_start(0, qall!)` | yes | **hangs** |\n| `timer_start(50, qall!)` | yes | **hangs** |\n| `timer_start(500, qall!)` | yes | **hangs** |\n| `vim.defer_fn(qall, 0)` | yes | **hangs** |\n| `vim.defer_fn(qall, 100)` | yes | **hangs** |\n| direct `qall!` | yes | exits fine |\n| `autocmd VimEnter * qall!` | yes | exits fine |\n| `timer_start(0, qall!)` | no (`--headless`) | exits fine |\n\n### 0.11.7 as child — everything works\n\nSame parent, same PTY setup — all of the above exit cleanly with 0.11.7.\n\n### Cross-version check\n\nThe bug is in the child, not the parent:\n\n| Child | Parent | PTY + timer_start(0) | Result |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 0.11.7 | 0.11.7 | yes | exits fine |\n| 0.11.7 | 0.12.1 | yes | exits fine |\n| 0.12.1 | 0.11.7 | yes | **hangs** |\n| 0.12.1 | 0.12.1 | yes | **hangs** |\n\nSo it's clearly something that changed in how 0.12 handles timers when running inside a PTY.\n\n## What's affected\n\nAt minimum `vim-startuptime` is broken — it uses `timer_start(0, {-> execute('qall!')})` to quit its profiling child processes. But anything that spawns nvim in a PTY job and expects timers to work would be affected too.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Neovim: 0.12.1, regression from 0.11.7\n- OS: EndeavourOS (Arch), Linux 6.19.11-arch1-1 x86_64\n- LuaJIT: 2.1.1774896198\n- Reproducible with `-u NONE` in any terminal",
