            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for the quick pointer! The DSR connection makes sense.\n\nTested the `:redraw` workaround — it reliably fixes the issue, including with `--startuptime`:\n\n```vim\n:call jobstart([v:progpath, '-u', 'NONE', '--startuptime', '/tmp/test.log', '-c',\n  \\ 'redraw | call timer_start(0, {-> execute(\"qall!\")})'], {'pty': v:true})\n```\n\nThis unblocks the event loop and timers fire as expected. I'll suggest it as a minimal fix for vim-startuptime.",
